itemListElement.name: The Original Food and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market

name: The Original Food and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market
description:
VOTED 10 BEST FOOD TOURS IN THE COUNTRY BY USA TODAY!

Join us for Seattle’s original food and cultural tour of Pike Place Market! On our signature tour, we’ll take you on a journey through the lively and bustling days in the heart of Seattle: Pike Place Market. While our guides give you the most delicious tastings we could find at EIGHT different partners, you'll also learn the history of the market and hear the stories of the small-batch food and craft producers that make this place one of Seattle's most beloved landmarks. This is Pike Place Market 101!

Savor Seattle is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market Preservation and Development Authority (PDA) to operate tours in the Pike Place Market Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting paid tours within its properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: top tour,
review.reviewBody: great tour by Nic and Tess. Excellent commentary on the history and under pinning culture of the markets couple with great tastings at a range of providers.  Highly recommended and a great introduction to the markets.

review.name: This was a great tour, very informative with delicious tastings.
review.reviewBody: Our guides Nick and Tessa were great. They were very knowledgeable and easy to talk to. The places we went were also very good and really opened our eyes to the delicious food available in Pike Market. We have been to nearly every place this afternoon to try more food from each place. Highly recommend.

review.name: Kacey is amazing!  Fantastic Food Tour!
review.reviewBody: Favorite thing we did!! Kacey was our tour guide. She previously worked in the market so she has the insider information!  Every stop we made was personalized!  Her knowledge of the restaurants and backgrounds of the vendors was incredible!!  This is well worth it!!

review.name: EO Vancouver Chapter Tenured Members Food Tour
review.reviewBody: Our group really enjoyed the walking tour & experience, learning about the history of not only the market but of many of the merchants we sampled.  Our guide, Tessa, was very knowledgeable & had a good sense of humour (needed with our group!).  Fun bonus was four of us including me got to catch the fish when thrown!  I’d recommend the tour for sure.  But dress warmly if it’s a bit chilly.

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: Frankie was an amazing guide today! She was informative, fun, and made the tour really entertaining. My 4 year old son went, and he had a great time.

review.name: Team Building Tour
review.reviewBody: Tessa was awesome and the food was amazing! The best bite was the fried fish. It was the perfect idea for a team building event.

review.name: Flying Fish and Rachael to the Rescue
review.reviewBody: Understanding the community and the culture behind Pike Place makes this so much more than just a food tour. Thanks Tessa for the great morning and the wonderful stories.

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: Tessa was an amazing guide! Very informative and amazing food! Would definitely recommend this tour to anyone visiting Seattle!

review.name: Would Never Be Able to Learn So Much on Your Own
review.reviewBody: This tour was amazing! It was so much more than just the food. The history of the marketplace was fascinating. We walked away having learned so much. Tessa and Frankie were fantastic! During the tour, our family made notes of where we wanted to go back and try, which we did. The tour was about 2.5 hours, or so, but we spent an additional 4 hours at the market on Easter Sunday. It was just incredible. There was great thought and detail put into the design of this tour. Highly recommend.

review.name: Amazing few hours with Skyler at Pike Place !
review.reviewBody: Skyler our guide was fabulous - knowledgable, witty and an incredible sense of humour. The tastings were great - really good range of flavours etc.

itemListElement.name: Private Professional Holiday Photoshoot in Seattle

name: Private Professional Holiday Photoshoot in Seattle
description:
Get ready for a unique experience to one of Seattle world famous locations! We will take a walk through this iconic spots which includes the Seattle most photo worthy monuments and some other hidden spots which most tourist may not know. 
Besides professional photography we will also give you every trick and tip to enjoy your holiday to the fullest! Come meet this city’s secrets and hidden corners with us while we capture your holiday’s precious moments. Looking forward to meeting you!

itemListElement.name: Leavenworth Christmas Lights Tour from Seattle

name: Leavenworth Christmas Lights Tour from Seattle
description:
Leavenworth is a great place to visit any time of the year, but exploring this magical town during the winter is an unforgettable adventure. 
Eye popping lights with music & entertainment, holiday characters for your photo ops, carolers, kids’ activities, roasting chestnuts, Santa photos and so much more…
Holiday lights are everywhere in the snow-covered Bavarian village of Leavenworth. There is an enchanted feeling in the air. From the festive German food to the Christmas decorations to carolers singing in the gazebo, whether you want to play outside in the snow or stay inside and enjoy great food.

review.name: Poor service, and dodgy shady policies / communications
review.reviewBody:
Unfortunately this is another one of those companies with shady policies and communications. I booked a tour and they confirmed the booking and was extremely responsive to take the business. Then I queried more detailed policies around how much notice they would give me if they cancelled on me for whatever reason, including what the guaranteed departure minimum numbers are, and they never replied even though I sent many follow-up emails. I know they read it, but they don't want to address the questions.

I read a number of reviews online saying that they cancel on you with very little notice if they don't get the required numbers and I wanted to verify if this was true by asking. Silence is not a good sign. 

Wasted my time researching, booking and querying. The last thing I want is a company not disclosing their policies upfront and become shady and silent when asked. These are big red flags. Having travelled for 15 years, I know when to "run for it" before the expletive hits the fan.

Lucky I booked through Viator and could cancel for free, which I did. I went to purchase a private tour instead for $250 more but I am happy to pay this additional fee for service from a transparent and honest company who disclosed to me their change/cancellation policies upfront, and who of course has guaranteed a tour since it is private. 

Avoid this company.

I know they won't like this review and will come here and probably make accusations of what a terrible customer I am and tell false stories and lies (this happened before when I tried to expose another company in Auckland NZ - "Auckland Scenic Tours" - please see my reviews), and they then responded with a series of untruths and lies to cover their backside. I won't be surprised if this happens here but it is my duty as a traveller and TripAdvisor reviewer to provide both great and bad reviews to protect other consumers and travellers.

Please message me if you want details about the "honest" company I have booked with instead.

itemListElement.name: From Seattle: Private Snoqualmie Falls Tour

name: From Seattle: Private Snoqualmie Falls Tour
description:
Just a short drive outside the Seattle city limits takes you to one of Washington’s top tourist attractions, Snoqualmie Falls. This world-famous waterfall plunges over 270 ft down into the Snoqualmie River and has been added to the National Register of Historic Places. Join us for breathtaking views and learn more about the creation of the falls, how it helps supply power to the Puget Sound region, what the falls mean to the native people and more. Options include both Upper and Lower Observation Decks, hike to the bottom, gift shop & more.

Expect professional, courteous service and an entertaining tour. We operate clean, well-maintained vehicles featuring leather interior and comfortable seating. Our Suburban seats 5 comfortably (6 max) with 1 front passenger seat, 2 captain’s chairs in the middle row, and bench seating for 3 (2 comfortably) in the rear. Includes heat & A/C, radio/CD, Auxiliary, USB port & limited rear luggage space. Special requests granted when possible.

itemListElement.name: Canada Vancouver Day Trip from Seattle USA

name: Canada Vancouver Day Trip from Seattle USA
description: Discover the vibrant city of Vancouver, one of the world's most livable cities, on this exciting tour. Explore iconic destinations like Stanley Park, Canada Place (with an optional FlyOver Canada 4D experience), Granville Island, and the historic Gastown Steam Clock. Pass by Chinatown and enjoy the stunning sights and culture of this Western Canadian gem. Travel requirements vary by citizenship, so ensure proper documentation is prepared in advance.

review.name: Jennifer Made Our Trip Truly Special!
review.reviewBody:
Unforgettable Tour with the Amazing Jennifer!

We had the pleasure of having Jennifer as our tour guide, and she was truly outstanding! From the moment we met her, she impressed us with her incredibly friendly and attentive manner. She made everyone feel welcomed and valued, creating a warm and relaxed atmosphere throughout the tour.

Jennifer is also an excellent driver — we always felt safe and comfortable on the road. What really stood out, though, was the wealth of information she shared with us. She brought the places we visited to life with her deep knowledge and passion, making the entire experience both educational and enjoyable.

If you're lucky enough to have Jennifer as your guide, you're in for a fantastic time.

review.name: An AMAZING day trip!
review.reviewBody:
I LOVED this day trip! We saw so many things and the weather was perfect,
which made it 10 times better. Mark was THE BEST! He was so knowledgeable and welcoming throughout the entire trip! I will be recommending this trip to all of my friends and family. Book it! You won’t be disappointed!

review.reviewBody: 每一個景點都很美，導遊小吳也都一直說明的很好，很祥細，問一些問題也都說的很清楚，大家也很合作，準時上車，很開心今天一天的旅遊！

review.name: Pleasant & accommodating tour guide.

review.name: Amazing Trip!

review.reviewBody: During our visit to Vancouver, Jereme was warm and thoughtful, responsible, and explained the tourist attractions vividly and clearly in both English and mandarin. We had such a memorable trip to Vancouver that we will forever remember. Thank you again Jereme! -Jack

review.name: Seamless Seattle to Vancouver Tour
review.reviewBody: We had a great experience on our day tour from Seattle to Vancouver with our guide, Chris. He was ok time and made sure everyone was comfortable throughout the trip. He regularly checked in with us, even asking if anyone needed bathroom breaks, which was much appreciated. Chris was also informative and shared interesting facts along the way. Overall, a smooth and enjoyable tour.

review.name: Excellent
review.reviewBody: It was a pleasure having Chris as our tour guide. He was patient and knowledgeable of the sites we visited. Everything was timed well, we had plenty of time for pictures and exploring. I would highly recommend Chris to friends and family. It’s a great experience to explore Vancouver within a day.
